### (1) Translation of the Story into English:

The King of Wei was plotting schemes and acting opportunistically, but none of his ministers could catch him. After returning from court, he was overjoyed. Wu Qi, a loyal minister, said to the king, "Have you heard of the words of King Zhuang of Chu? They circulated among your ministers, right?" The King of Wei asked, "What were the words of King Zhuang of Chu?" Wu Qi replied, "King Zhuang of Chu was plotting schemes and acting opportunistically, but none of his ministers could catch him. After returning from court, he was overjoyed. Lord Shen and his ministers asked, 'Why is the king overjoyed?' King Zhuang of Chu said, 'He is not a good ruler, but his ministers cannot catch him. This is why he is overjoyed. Among them, there is a man named Yu, who said, 'Those who consider themselves teachers are kings, those who consider themselves friends are emperors, those who are doubtful are cautious, and those who plot schemes without thinking for themselves will perish.' Now, with a ruler as unqualified as Yu, and his ministers unable to catch him, is our country at risk of collapse? This is why he is overjoyed.'" The King of Chu was overjoyed, and the King of Wei was overjoyed too. The King of Wei bowed again and said, "Heavenly Father, you have corrected our mistakes."

